    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels like such a lie. like, if you knew for a fact that a house was on fire and it was beyond saving, would you really stay inside just to \"counter the momentum\" of the flames? wouldn't it just be more rational to just leave? it feels like staying is just choosing to suffer unnecessarily when the outcome is already decided. it's like... why stay for a show that's already ended and everyone is just waiting for the lights to go out?",
